I have a route that signs user out of their account. This works if the user closes their browser and opens it again. Microsoft will not prompt and automatically signs the user in if the user uses the same window to sign in.

```
@auth.route('/signout')
def sign_out():
  for account in msal_app.get_accounts():
    msal_app.remove_account(account)
  session.clear()
```

Do I need to clear anything else etc to sign the user out completely?
